description:
I Duties and Responsibilities

Make market research and analysis on potential customers and competitors;
Identify trends and customer needs
Build a short, medium, long-term sales pipeline in accordance with targets;
Develop new B2B opportunities in Europe (France as priority);
Create and give presentations to clients and internal executives;
Negotiate contract terms with clients and communicate with stakeholders;
Monitor project management to ensure contracts are executed as agreed;
Interact and liaise with merchandisers & clients;
Build, develop and maintain a solid and trusting relationship with clients;
Resolve key client issues and complaints;
Produce regular sales forecast reports & propose new sales strategies to stimulate growth.

II Skills and Qualifications

General:

Bachelor Degree or above in sales, business or equivalent;
Knowledge in Small Domestic Appliance (SDA) and outdoor furniture would be an advantage;
Familiarity with the trading industry (sourcing, production, logistics and supply-chain management);
Good communicator, ability to interact & collaborate with cross-functional teams;
Good listener, problem-solver, propose solutions and follow-up;  
Proficiency with word processing, excel spreadsheet and presentation software;
Strong analytical skills and experience with reporting and data analysis;
Fluent in both English and French. Any other language will be a plus;
Positive energy, entrepreneurial mindset, proactive multi-tasker; good team player;
Be results-oriented and have a taste for challenge;
Strategic thinker, ambitious and self-managed;
Desire to improve processes, dedication to high-quality work.

Sales & Business Development

Experience in B2B and B2C sales with strong negotiation skills;
Ability to manage multiple projects at the same time in a fast-paced environment;
Familiarity with project management methodologies;
Ability and willingness to travel for meetings with prospective and existing clients;
Proficiency in using a CRM and ERP.

Responsibilities:

Visit customers and reporting to management team in a regular basis;
Promote services to clients and customers, network will be an advantage;
Communicate and reflect customer requirements;
Work with the team to achieve sales targets;
Update customer’s status and market information to management team, etc.
Any other duties as assigned by the Supervisor/ Manager of the Employer or other associated or subsidiary company(ies) of the Employer.

 Qualification

Bachelor’s Degree in Science or Biology related discipline is basic requirement, Master Degree or above preferred
Candidate with more experience will be considered as Senior Sales Representative or Sales Manage
Good interpersonal, presentation and communication skills, and teamwork
Meticulous, well-organized, responsible, and self-motivated.
Proficiency in written and spoken English & Chinese (both Cantonese and Mandarin)

Responsibilities:

Support and deliver the Training Delivery Guide in Customer Relationship Management (CRM) Training;
Collaborate with Regional, Country Sales, and Customer Service teams to determine and evaluate their training requirements and effectiveness, as well as generate and distribute reports;
Participate in the User Acceptance Testing (UAT) for Customer Relationship Management (CRM) and assist in guiding designated users among the region.

 Requirements:

Bachelor Degree in any discipline, major in shipping, logistics or business management is highly preferred;
Minimum 10 years of relevant experience;
Strong interpersonal skills such as communication and listening;
Technical skills including a competent understanding of customer service department workflows;
Experience in training or teaching is a must;
Willingness to learn and keep improving the knowledge;
Knowledge in CRM system (preferably Salesforce) is an advantage but not a mandatory requirement;
Familiar with Microsoft Office or Google suite, e.g. Word, Excel, PowerPoint, G-sheets, G-Docs, G-Slides;
Good command in spoken and written English and Chinese, Mandarin is a plus.

Job Responsibilities:
• Supervise Sales team in China for Promotion, and sales and marketing;
• Liaise with the China manufacturing facilities for the sample development as well as delivery schedule
• Generate potential sales in new accounts that meet target budget ;
• Prepare & deliver professional presentations, proposal and marketing materials to potential client;
• Positive thinking, high degree of self-motivation, reliable and result-oriented;
• travel to mainland when required;
Requirement:
• 3 years marketing and sales experience in mainland market.
• F.5 or above.
• Good command of English, Chinese & Mandarin
Salary offer: HK$18,000 - HK$22,000 or above (depends on experience)
Interested parties, please apply together with a detailed resume, stating current and expected salary, and send it via Apply Now
APPLY NOW.  (Reference no and Company name).  Attractive remuneration will be offered in commensurate with qualifications and experience.
All personal information received will be treated in strict confidence for employment purpose only. Your application can be considered as unsuccessful if you have not been reached within 3 months. On the other hand, it may be transferred to other companies of our group for job openings. Unsuccessful applications will be destroyed for a period not more than 12 months.

Job Duties:



Handle incoming calls, emails on all customer enquiries in a proactive and positive manner;
Response promptly to client’s products and service inquiries;
Resolve client’s complaints;
Responsible for various general office administrative duties including but not limited to data entry, arrange service schedules, etc.;
Organize and distribute incoming & outing correspondences and courier documents;
Handle ad hoc tasks as assigned by Supervisor

Requirement:

HKALE/HKDSE or equivalent;
1-2 years related experience;
Good command of spoken and written English and Chinese.  Knowledge of Mandarin is preferred;
Good interpersonal skills, well-organized, self-motivated and customer-oriented;
Proficient in using MS Office, such as Word, Excel, Outlook etc;
Responsible, polite, punctual and willing to learn;
Immediate availability preferred;



