Responsibilities:

Be the AGENT to make change happen and make GREEN common!
To raise the awareness of Green Monday, Green Common and its affiliated brands, so do the awareness of health and sustainability;
To increase demand for plant-based products in overseas market;
To broaden the reach of F&B and retail channels that carry plant-based options;
Work with overseas distributors/ partners closely to strategize sales plan;
Explore partnership with different channels including hospitality & food service industry;
Perform market and sales channel analysis as part of market research;
Wholesales marketing – collaborating with wholesale accounts on marketing events at partners’ stores, and other incentive projects;
Create, maintain and update sales kits, marketing materials for wholesale, order forms and other related sales tools;
To support ad-hoc duties as assigned.

Requirements:

Passionate in promoting green lifestyle (knowledge in vegetarian/vegan product is a plus)
Degree holder or above in Hospitality or Business Development;
At least 3 years’ working experience in Business Development or F&B industry is preferable;
Have project experience is definitely an advantage;
Preferred oversea experience either for study or work related
Excellent command in spoken and written English;
Proactive, responsible, organized and ability to work in a fast-paced environment;
A good team player with good interpersonal and communication skills.

Interested parties please apply with full resume stating availability, current and expected salaries by clicking "APPLY NOW"

Job Type: Full-time

Schedule:

Monday to Friday

Education:

Bachelor's Degree (Preferred)

Experience:

F&B Industry: 3 years (Preferred)
Business development: 3 years (Preferred)

Language:

English (Preferred)

Work Remotely:

No

JOIN US TO MAKE CHANGE HAPPEN MAKE GREEN COMMON

Green Monday is a multi-faceted award-winning social venture group that aims to tackle climate change, global food insecurity and public health issues. The once-a-week plant-based meal philosophy of Green Monday is practiced by over 1.6 million people at its origin in Hong Kong, and has spread to over 30 countries.

Green Common is the pioneer and leader in the “better-for-you” category in Asia, and are the distributor to many global leading brands in plant-based food industry (Beyond Meat & OmniPork etc), while Green Monday is an advocacy and movement platform to educate and mobilize people towards a healthy, sustainable plant-based diet. We are expanding our international outreach to other parts of Asia, to champion the Green Monday movement as well as introducing global food-tech innovations.

Responsibilities:
Be the AGENT to make change happen and make GREEN common!
To raise the awareness of Green Monday, Green Common and its affiliated brands, so do the awareness of health and sustainability;
To increase demand for plant-based products in overseas market;
To broaden the reach of F&B and retail channels that carry plant-based options;
Work with overseas distributors/ partners closely to strategize sales plan;
Explore partnership with different channels including hospitality & food service industry;
Perform market and sales channel analysis as part of market research;
Wholesales marketing – collaborating with wholesale accounts on marketing events at partners’ stores, and other incentive projects;
Create, maintain and update sales kits, marketing materials for wholesale, order forms and other related sales tools;
To support ad-hoc duties as assigned.

Requirements:
Passionate in promoting green lifestyle (knowledge in vegetarian/vegan product is a plus)
Degree holder or above in Hospitality or Business Development;
At least 3 years’ working experience in Business Development or F&B industry is preferable;
Have project experience is definitely an advantage;
Preferred oversea experience either for study or work related
Excellent command in spoken and written English;
Proactive, responsible, organized and ability to work in a fast-paced environment;
A good team player with good interpersonal and communication skills.

Interested parties please apply with full resume stating availability, current and expected salaries by clicking "APPLY NOW"
We are an equal opportunity employer and welcome applications from qualified candidates. All information provided will be treated in strict confidence by authorized personnel and will be used only for recruitment related purpose. Applicants who do not hear from us within 6 weeks may consider their application unsuccessful. All personal data of unsuccessful applications will be destroyed after 6 months.

Job Duties:

Manage and monitor the company‘s official website, Facebook, Instagram etc;
Work on Powerpoints, translations of documents and/or videos;
Responsible to the whole process of workshops from planning, coordination and post event management;
Coordinate with difference trainers in workshop preparation;
Answer inquiries from members and guests; 
Data entry and filling of member applications forms;
Ad hoc duties and assignment.

Requirement:

F.7 or above, preferably to have 1-2 years of event planning experiences;
An active and passionate team member with good team spirit;
Good communication skills and customer service manner with good telephone manner;
Good writing proficiency in English and Chinese;
