Able to work under stress and ad hoc assignments
Flexible working hours for occasionally events.

Please send full resume & expected salary to us.

Handling in-store and e-commerce customer enquiries and complaints via all communication channels, including but not limited to email, live chat, telephone and face-to-face; including products’ promotion, logistics, products return;
Support the team in sales activities, including order processing and post-sales coordination;
Responsible for in-store e-commerce work station operations, including maintain the e-commerce system, handle in-store pickup orders and provide excellent customer service at store.
Responsible for the administration support including data input and coupon/GWP redemption;
Responsible for Customer Service reports;
Assist in handling ad-hoc assignments if needed.

Requirements:

Higher Diploma or above;
1 year relevant experience from customer service field would be an advantage;
Detail-minded, positive and proactive working attitude, with strong customer service mindset;
Good command of both spoken & written English and Mandarin;
Shift duty is required;
NO sales target need to be achieved;
Fresh graduate is also welcome to apply;
Candidates with more experience will be considered as senior position.

We offer:

6.5 days off per month
17 Public Holidays
11 Annual Leave
Attendance bonus
Shift allowance
Medical benefits

We offer excellent career prospects, competitive salary and fringe benefits to the right candidate. Please apply in strict confidence by sending personal resume together with salary expected and date availability by email: careers @ harveynichols. com .hk or Whatsapp 9828-0637.

We are an equal opportunity employer and welcome applications from all qualified candidates.  Personal data provided by job applicants will be used strictly in accordance with our personal data policy and for recruitment purposes only.  Candidates not notified within eight weeks may consider their application unsuccessful.  All related information will be kept in our file for up to 24 months.  A copy of our Personal Information Collection Statement will be provided upon request by contacting our Human Resources Division.

Job Responsibilities:
Responsible for sales of home learning products to customers;
Responsible for the sales target;
Deliver professional selling and post selling service for our users;
Actively participate in customer related activity and sales promotion event.
Job Requirements:


Degree or above with minimum 3 years’ relevant selling experience;
Collaborate with team to achieve better result;
Strong presentation and communication skills;
High motivation for sales;
Relevant experience in working early childhood is definite an advantage;
Candidates with more experience will be considered as Senior Sales Executive. 
We are committed to supporting diversity in our workforce, and ensuring an inclusive environment where all employees can thrive. We seek to employ a workforce representative of the markets that we serve, and encourage applications from people of all ethnic, cultural and social backgrounds.  
Applications, including curriculum vitae and expected salary, should be sent by clicking “APPLY NOW”.
Personal data will be used for recruitment purposes only.

Main Job Tasks & Responsibilities:

To provide general training administrative support, e.g. generating reports, updating training materials, SOP, guide books
To manage and support operation of Learning Project;
To assist in pre- and post-training logistics with internal or external parties to ensure smooth delivery of training initiative;
To assist in preparing training materials, including in-class training and e-learning/ mobile app learning materials in alignment with the prevailing operational developments and corporate training directives;
To manage customers' database, prepare and deliver promotion materials to potential customers and conduct marketing survey;
To conduct training evaluation and prepare training statistics in regular basis;
To assist in creating development plan for training service of the Association and promotion strategies;

Qualifications & Experience:

Bachelor’s Degree holder, 5 passes in HKCEE
1-2 years relevant experience in learning & development
Proficiency in both spoken and written Chinese and English
Good interpersonal and communication skills
Proactive and willing to work overtime, under pressure, and with
minimum supervision
Self-motivated, quick response, able to work independently and
under pressure
Proficient computer skills including Word, Excel and PowerPoint
Immediate availability preferred
